## General timeline settings

The **Timeline (VX)** widget can be used to add social activity to your site.

General settings related to this widget can be configured in **WP admin  Timeline  Settings**

## General

**User timeline:**

Control the visibility of posts shared by a user in their timeline.

- Public: Visible to everyone
- Logged-in: Visible to all logged in users
- Followers: Visible to followers only
- Customers: Visible to customers only
- Private: Visible to the user only

**Timeline feed**

Some general settings related to Timeline widget including

- Posts per page
- Replies per page
- Enable reposts and quotes
- Show author username

**Actions**

- Purge Timeline related stats. Useful if you are not seeing up to date data related to timeline or followers

## Statuses

**Create status settings**

- Max length (in characters)
- Allow image uploads
- Max image count
- Max image size (in kB)
- Allowed file formats
- Allow editing of published posts

**Display**

- Display Read more toggle after (in characters)

**Quotes**

- Truncate content after (in characters)

**Post rate limiting:**

Limit the number of statuses a user can publish in a time period

- Minimum time between posts (in seconds)
- Maximum number of posts allowed in an hour
- Maximum number of posts allowed in a day

## Replies

**Create reply settings**

- Max length (in characters)
- Allow image uploads
- Max image count
- Max image size (in kB)
- Allowed file formats
- Allow editing of published replies

**Display**

- Display Read more toggle after (in characters)
- Max reply depth. (When max depth is reached, further replies are displayed as mentions)

**Reply rate limiting**

Limit the number of replies a user can publish in a time period

- Minimum time between replies (in seconds)
- Maximum number of replies allowed in an hour
- Maximum number of replies allowed in a day

## More settings

Moderation and other settings are covered in a dedicated article
